      "message": "Thanks for the explanation.\n\nOff hand, having another type for all those variants is a bit odd -- doubt we would add it if we didn\u0027t already have it. Sure, we can see how complicated it would be to remove it in a separate experiment. (I do find that how complicated something is for our gms/tests is not always a good measure for how it will be to update real clients).",
